		"description": "<p>While you are attuned to and wearing a transforming cloak, you gain resistance to a type of damage and you can use an action to activate an elemental form that lasts for 1 hour, until you fall unconscious, or you use a bonus action to end it.</p><p>Once you have used the cloak to take on an elemental form, you cannot use that property again until you have finished a long rest.</p><hr class=\"a5e-rule u-my-md\"><p><em>This cloak looks like iridescent dragonfly wings that appear to flutter when seen out of the corner of the eye.</em></p><hr class=\"a5e-rule u-my-md\"><p>While your air form is active you gain:</p><ul><li><p>a fly speed of 30 feet (hover)</p><p></p></li><li><p>you do not need to breathe</p><p></p></li><li><p>you do not provoke opportunity attacks</p><p></p></li><li><p>you can pass through spaces at least half an inch wide without squeezing.</p></li></ul>",
